# NetBird Deployment Tasks

## Phase 1: Prerequisites & Cleanup
- [/] Check port 8080 usage and free if needed
- [ ] Install jq if not present
- [ ] Stop/remove any existing NetBird containers
- [ ] Verify SSL certificates exist
- [ ] Check port 3478 availability

## Phase 2: Run Official Getting-Started Script
- [ ] Set NETBIRD_DOMAIN and run getting-started.sh
- [ ] Select Nginx option [2]
- [ ] Verify generated files

## Phase 3: Configure Nginx Reverse Proxy
- [ ] Create /etc/nginx/sites-available/netbird config
- [ ] Update SSL cert paths
- [ ] Enable site and test config
- [ ] Reload Nginx

## Phase 4: Start Services & Validate
- [ ] docker compose up -d
- [ ] Verify all containers running
- [ ] Test dashboard URL
- [ ] Test API endpoint

## Phase 5: Initial Admin Setup
- [ ] Access /setup page
- [ ] Create admin account

## Phase 6: Azure AD Integration (post-deployment)
- [ ] Add Azure AD via Dashboard UI

## Phase 7: Client Onboarding
- [ ] Generate setup key
- [ ] Connect client
